This article is about an executive order signed by President Barack Obama in 2012. The order establishes an order of succession within the Department of Agriculture in the event that both the Secretary and the Deputy Secretary of Agriculture are unable to perform their duties. The order lists the officials within the department who will act as and perform the functions and duties of the Secretary of Agriculture during such periods. It also specifies exceptions and revokes a previous executive order on the same topic. The article concludes by stating that the order does not create any legal rights or benefits enforceable against the United States or any other party.